t vorgenommen, um dem Leser eine ausführliche Ausgabe zur Verfügung zu stellen.  aQ. Curtius Rufus (1st century CE) is one of the most important historians of Alexander the Great. However, existing editions in use today are philologically unsatisfactory for a number of reasons, and the aim of this work is to present a sounder text. This edition is the first to pay adequate attention to the second family of manuscripts, as well as placing the conjectures of the respective philologists in their correct context.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Latin.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGeneralszGreecevBiographyvEarly works to 1800. 4aAlexander (der Große). 4aHandschrift. 4aHistoriographie. 4aTextkritik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAlexander (the Great).  aHistoriography.  aManuscripts.  aTextual Criticism.1 aLucarini, Carlo M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN0 cprintz978311020116140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311097293140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110972931423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110972931/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014